('32505', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 40'),
('32505', '2', 'With the side of a large knife, mash the garlic cloves with 1 tablespoon of kosher salt to make a coarse paste.'),
('32505', '3', 'Transfer the paste to a small bowl. Stir in the coriander, thyme, oregano, 1 tablespoon of salt, 2 tablespoons of coarsely ground black pepper and 1/2 cup of the olive oil until incorporated.'),
('32505', '4', 'On a work surface, rub the garlic-herb oil all over the butterflied pork. With the fatty side up, fold the pork under itself into thirds and transfer to a roasting pan. Roast the pork for 40 minutes. Reduce the oven temperature to 300 and roast the pork for about 2 hours and 20 minutes longer, until an instant-read thermometer inserted in the center registers 16'),
('32505', '5', 'Meanwhile, bring a large saucepan of salted water to a boil.'),
('32505', '6', 'Add the fava beans and boil until the skins loosen, about 2 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the favas to a work surface. peel off and discard the tough skins and transfer the favas to a bowl. Alternatively, boil the frozen edamame for 2 minutes and transfer to a bowl.'),
('32505', '7', 'Add the carrots to the saucepan and boil until tender, about 4 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the carrots to the bowl.'),
('32505', '8', 'Add the peas and cook until tender, about 2 minutes. if using frozen, boil just until hot, 30 seconds.'),
('32505', '9', 'Drain the peas and transfer to the bowl.'),
('32505', '10', 'In the same saucepan, melt the butter in 1 tablespoon of the olive oil. Stir in the vegetables and season with salt and pepper. Cook over moderate heat until just heated through. Stir in the 3 tablespoons of chopped herbs.'),
('32505', '11', 'Transfer the pork to a carving board and let rest for at least 10 minutes. Strain the pan juices into a small saucepan and skim off the fat.'),
('32505', '12', 'Add the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil and balsamic vinegar and season with salt and pepper. Bring to a simmer, cover and keep hot.'),
('32505', '13', 'Thickly slice the pork across the grain and transfer to plates.'),
('32505', '14', 'Serve with the vegetables, passing the sauce at the table.'),
('32508', '1', 'Wash and grate your zucchini, yellow squash and sweet potato.Chop your red pepper and green onion.In a blender, toss in your cashews, water, garbanzo flour, apple cider vinegar and salt. Blend until super creamy. In a large bowl place your squash, zucchini, sweet potato, pepper and onion.'),
('32508', '2', 'Add the remaining ingredients and your cashew mixture. Carefully fold together until well mixed.'),
('32508', '3', 'Heat a skillet over low-medium heat, add coconut oil and evenly coat bottom of pan. Sprinkle a pinch of Garbanzo flour into the pan where you will be spooning on a veggie cake. This creates more crunch. Using 3-4 spoonfuls of your veggie cake mix, create a cake on top of your sprinkle. Repeat until you have 3-4 cakes in your pan. Sprinkle garbanzo flour on top of all cakes.'),
('32508', '4', 'Let each cake slowly brown in your pan for about 15-20 minutes on each side. Flip carefully by sneaking the spatula entirely under each cake before flipping. Once cakes are browned on both sides, you can turn up the heat a bit to brown further if you like. The slow browning on both sides binds the cakes very well.'),
('32508', '5', 'Serve with a wedge of lemon.'),
('32509', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 35'),
('32509', '2', 'Put the whole garlic cloves and whole, unpeeled shallots on a rimmed baking sheet.'),
('32509', '3', 'Drizzle lightly with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.'),
('32509', '4', 'Bake the garlic for 15 minutes, or until softened. transfer to a plate.'),
('32509', '5', 'Bake the shallots for 30 minutes, until softened.'),
('32509', '6', 'Let the garlic and shallots cool, then peel the shallots. Turn the oven temperature up to 42'),
('32509', '7', 'Preheat a grill pan and lightly oil it.'),
('32509', '8', 'Put the corn on the grill, cover loosely with foil and cook over moderately high heat, turning occasionally, until lightly charred and crisp-tender, about 20 minutes.'),
('32509', '9', 'Let cool slightly, then cut the kernels from the cobs.'),
('32509', '10', 'In a saucepan, heat 1 tablespoon of the olive oil.'),
('32509', '11', 'Add the sliced garlic and shallots and cook over moderate heat until softened, 4 minutes. Scrape the shallots and garlic into a blender.'),
('32509', '12', 'Add the marjoram and vinegar and puree. With the machine on, add 1/4 cup of the olive oil. Season the vinaigrette with salt and pepper.'),
('32509', '13', 'In a small saucepan of boiling water, cook the fava beans until just tender, about 2 minutes.'),
('32509', '14', 'Drain and peel. In a large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of the vegetable oil until shimmering. Season the veal chops with salt and pepper.'),
('32509', '15', 'Add 2 of the chops to the skillet and cook over moderately high heat until browned, about 3 minutes per side.'),
('32509', '16', 'Transfer the chops to a rimmed baking sheet and repeat with the remaining 2 chops and remaining 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil.'),
('32509', '17', 'Bake the chops for about 15 minutes, until just pink in the center.'),
('32509', '18', 'Meanwhile, in a medium saucepan of boiling salted water, cook the orzo until al dente.'),
('32509', '19', 'Drain, reserving 1/4 cup of the cooking water. Return the saucepan to the stove.'),
('32509', '20', 'Add the butter and the charred corn and cook over moderately high heat until heated through. Stir in the orzo and the reserved cooking water, then stir in the Parmesan. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('32509', '21', 'In a small skillet, heat the remaining 1 tablespoon of olive oil.'),
('32509', '22', 'Add the shallots, garlic cloves and fava beans and season with salt and pepper. Cook over moderately high heat until warmed through, about 1 minute.'),
('32509', '23', 'Spoon the orzo onto plates and top with the veal chops. Spoon the shallots, garlic and favas alongside. Spoon the vinaigrette around the veal and serve.'),
('32510', '1', 'Drain the beans.'),
('32510', '2', 'Place them in a large saucepan and add enough fresh water to cover. Coarsely chop 1 of the onions and 3 of the garlic cloves and add to the pan. Bring to a boil, skimming off any foam. Reduce the heat and cover. Simmer 1 hour, or until the beans are soft.'),
('32510', '3', 'Drain the beans and vegetables, reserving the cooking liquid.'),
('32510', '4', 'Transfer the mixture to a food processor and add the cilantro, parsley, mint, and cumin. Pure, adding enough of the reserved cooking liquid to moisten the mixture. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('32510', '5', 'Transfer to a dish and keep warm.'),
('32510', '6', 'Meanwhile, slice the remaining onions.'),
('32510', '7', 'Heat 1 tbsp oil over medium-high heat.'),
('32510', '8', 'Add the onions and cook, stirring often, for about 12 minutes, or until they are dark golden and slightly caramelized. Chop the garlic, stir into the onions, and cook for 1 minute more.'),
('32510', '9', 'Spread the fried onions and garlic over the pure and drizzle with the lemon juice and remaining oil.'),
('32510', '10', 'Garnish with additional cilantro and parsley and serve.'),
('32510', '11', 'Spread the fried onions and garlic over the pure and drizzle with the lemon juice and remaining oil.'),
('32510', '12', 'Garnish with additional cilantro and parsley and serve.'),
