('32525', '1', 'Blanch fava beans in a pot of boiling well-salted water 1 minute, then transfer with a slotted spoon to an ice bath to stop cooking.'),
('32525', '2', 'Transfer favas with slotted spoon to a small bowl.'),
('32525', '3', 'Cook Romano beans in same pot of boiling water, stirring occasionally, until just tender, about 5 minutes, then transfer to ice bath to stop cooking.'),
('32525', '4', 'Drain well and transfer to a bowl.'),
('32525', '5', 'Cook green beans in same pot until just tender, 6 to 7 minutes, then transfer to ice bath.'),
('32525', '6', 'Add to Romano beans.'),
('32525', '7', 'Gently peel skins from fava beans (it''s not necessary to peel edamame, if using), then add to other beans.'),
('32525', '8', 'Cut basil into very thin shreds.'),
('32525', '9', 'Cook garlic in oil with a rounded 1/4 teaspoon each of salt and pepper in a 12-inch heavy skillet over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 1 minute.'),
('32525', '10', 'Add beans, water, and zest and cook, stirring occasionally, until heated through. Stir in basil and 2 1/2 teaspoons lemon juice and remove from heat. Season with salt and additional lemon juice if desired.'),
('32525', '11', 'Serve beans warm or at room temperature.'),
('32526', '1', 'Blanch beans in a 2-quart pot of boiling water 1 minute, then drain in a sieve and immediately transfer to a bowl of ice and cold water to stop cooking. Gently peel off skins (it''s not necessary to peel edamame, if using).'),
('32527', '1', 'Pour the rice into boiling salted water. Boil hard for about 14 minutes, until it is almost but not entirely tender.'),
('32527', '2', 'Drain and put back into the pan. Stir in 3 tablespoons of the oil, the herbs, and salt and pepper to taste.'),
('32527', '3', 'Put the lid on and leave the pan on very low heat for the rice to steam for about 15 minutes, or until tender.'),
('32527', '4', 'Boil the fava beans in salted water for a few minutes, until tender, then drain. Stir gently into the rice with the remaining oil.'),
('32527', '5', 'Serve hot or cold with the yogurt, beaten with crushed garlic if you like and a little salt, poured over.'),
('32527', '6', 'var article'),
('32527', '7', 'Type_27_data = {}.'),
('32527', '8', 'article'),
('32527', '9', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0.'),
('32530', '1', 'Heat a large deep cast iron skillet over medium-high heat on stove top.'),
('32530', '2', 'Add a little oil and allow it to become hot.'),
('32530', '3', 'Add pork and cook for about 5 minutes, turning to ensure even browning on all sides.'),
('32530', '4', 'Drain excess oil.'),
('32530', '5', 'Add remaining ingredients and bring to a gentle simmer. Cook uncovered for two hours at 350 degrees F. Turn meat over halfway through cooking. The meat is cooked once tender, but not falling apart.To serve, place meat on chopping board and carve into 1/4 inch slices.'),
('32530', '6', 'Place a spoonful of fava bean puree onto a plate and top with vegetable ragout and a few slices of braised pork followed by roasted onions.'),
('32531', '1', 'In a large saucepan bring water to a boil.  Rinse rice. stir into boiling water. Boil just until rice rises to the surface of the water.'),
('32531', '2', 'Drain rice and return it to the saucepan.  Stir in the oil and water.'),
('32531', '3', 'Mix in the dill, parsley, cilantro, fava beans, turmeric, cinnamon, salt and pepper.'),
('32531', '4', 'Cook the rice over medium heat for 5 minutes.'),
('32531', '5', 'Reduce heat to the lowest setting. Cover and simmer for 40 to 45 minutes.  Note:  It''s normal to end up with crispy rice (called Tadig) on the bottom of the pot after cooking. it''s delicious.'),
('32538', '1', 'Have ready a large bowl of ice and cold water. Boil edamame or fava beans in a large pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, 1 to 3 minutes.'),
('32538', '2', 'Transfer with a slotted spoon to ice water. Shell edamame, or peel tough outer skins from fava beans.'),
('32538', '3', 'Bring potatoes and enough salted water to cover by 1 1/2 inches to a boil and cook at a bare simmer until almost tender, 15 to 20 minutes. (Potatoes will continue to cook a bit after being removed from water. Be careful not to overcook or potatoes will break apart when sliced.)'),
('32538', '4', 'Transfer with a slotted spoon to ice water to cool.'),
('32538', '5', 'Drain well.'),
('32538', '6', 'While potatoes are cooking, trim haricots verts and halve diagonally crosswise. Cook in 2 batches in a large pot of boiling salted water until just tender, 3 to 4 minutes (regular green beans will take longer to cook).'),
('32538', '7', 'Transfer to ice water to cool.'),
('32538', '8', 'Drain well.'),
('32538', '9', 'Just before serving, cut potatoes into 1/3-inch-thick slices and toss all ingredients together in a large bowl with salt and pepper to taste.'),
('32546', '1', 'In two separate pans of boiling water, cook the beans until tender, about 4 and 8 minutes for the favas and cranberry beans, respectively.'),
('32546', '2', 'Drain and refresh the beans under cold running water, and remove the outer skins from the favas.'),
('32546', '3', 'In a medium saucepan, boil the onion, bay leaves, carrot, and celery in 6 cups of water for 20 minutes.'),
('32546', '4', 'Add the shrimp and cook just until opaque throughout, about 1 minute.'),
('32546', '5', 'Remove and drain the shrimp and allow them to cool.'),
('32546', '6', 'In a serving bowl, whisk together the olive oil, vinegar, and salt and pepper.'),
('32546', '7', 'Add the beans and shrimp, and toss to coat the solids thoroughly.'),
('32546', '8', 'Serve warm as an appetizer.'),
